p <small>(Click the item below to reveal more info. Click the image to preview a bigger size.)</small>

+details( 'Homepage and Blog page', topic_href+'-'+(++index) )
	p Set up your website <a href="#pages">front and blog page</a> in WordPress #[+mark( 'nav', 'Appearance', 'Customize', 'Static Front Page' )] settings (or in #[+mark( 'nav', 'Settings', 'Reading' )]).
	+back_to( 'image', topic_href )

+details( 'Page featured image', topic_href+'-'+(++index) )
	p Page featured image is set as background of intro section. Or you can set a different intro background image using <a href="#custom-fields">custom fields</a> (useful for child pages when you use page featured image in the list of child pages and the custom intro image on the actual child page).
	p Featured image is also displayed in the list of child pages. Please see <a href="#pages">"List child pages" page template</a> for more details.
	p Please see FAQ section for more <a href="#image-sizes">information on image sizes</a>.
	+back_to( 'image', topic_href )

+details( 'Page excerpt', topic_href+'-'+(++index) )
	p If you set a <a href="#page-excerpt">page excerpt</a>, this will be displayed in intro section of the page.
	p Excerpt is also used in a list of child pages. Please see <a href="#pages">"List child pages" page template</a> for more details.
	+back_to( 'image', topic_href )

+details( 'Intro Widgets', topic_href+'-'+(++index) )
	p A <a href="#sidebars">widget area</a>, its content can be set in #[+mark( 'nav', 'Appearance', 'Customize', 'Widgets' )].
	p Colors can be <a href="#customizer">customized</a> in #[+mark( 'nav', 'Appearance', 'Customize', 'Theme Options', 'Colors: Intro' )].
	p You can control the appearance with a <a href="#pages">page template</a> or a <a href="#custom-fields">custom field</a> and <a href="#manage-sidebars">Content Aware Sidebars plugin</a>.
	+back_to( 'image', topic_href )

+details( 'Fullwidth or sidebar', topic_href+'-'+(++index) )
	p The theme displays pages as fullwidth, with no sidebar by default. If you would like to display a sidebar on a page, use a specific <a href="#pages">page template</a>.
	p Sidebar is a <a href="#sidebars">widget area</a>, its content can be set in #[+mark( 'nav', 'Appearance', 'Customize', 'Widgets' )].
	p If you would like to replace sidebar on a specific page with a different one or just remove it, use <a href="#manage-sidebars"><strong>Content Aware Sidebars</strong> plugin</a>. It is a great way to control and alter your website layout.
	+back_to( 'image', topic_href )

+details( 'Child pages list', topic_href+'-'+(++index) )
	p Please see <a href="#pages">"List child pages" page template</a> for more details.
	+back_to( 'image', topic_href )

+details( 'Page with no header and footer', topic_href+'-'+(++index) )
	p If you are creating a special landing page and would like to remove header and footer from the page use the <a href="#pages">"Blank" page template</a>.
	+back_to( 'image', topic_href )

+details( 'Page builder', topic_href+'-'+(++index) )
	p For creating a more complex page layouts please use a (<a href="#any-page-builder">any</a>) page builder plugin (we recommend using powerful, optimized and easy to use <a href="#beaver-builder"><strong>Beaver Builder</strong> page builder plugin</a>).
	+back_to( 'image', topic_href )

+back_to( 'topics', 'anatomy' )
